<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1600,2023]" pageId="3" pageNumber="671">Measurements (n = 6): Total length: 6.84 (7.24) 7.63; width: 3.63 (3.95) 4.21. Head. Length: 1.32 (1.37) 1.45; width: 1.74 (1.84) 1.89; interocular space: 0.95 (1.06) 1.13; antennal segment lengths: 0.45 (0.48) 0.53; II: 0.82 (0.87) 0.92; III: 0.42 (0.43) 0.45; IV: 0.63 (0.70) 0.76; V: 0.74 (0.78) 0.82. Pronotum. Length: 1.37 (1.45) 1.50; width at base: 3.10 (3.39) 3.68.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1600,2023]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1436,151,249]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="672" pageId="3" pageNumber="671">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,466,1888,1914]" pageId="3" pageNumber="671">Diagnostic characters.</emphasis>
General color blackish with well-marked punctures and smooth pale yellowish areas, particularly along the clavo-corial suture, margins of pronotum and exocorium (
<figureCitation box="[1042,1110,1924,1951]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1742,1766]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,273,1719]" captionTargetId="figure-64@4.[151,1435,273,1719]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–12. Hyperbius geniculatus (Signoret). 7. Dorsal View. 8. Head. Fig. 9. Metapleura. 10. Pendergrast’s Organ. 11. Female genitalia. Caudal view. 12. Male genitalia. Caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4692793" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4692793/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="671">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Head (
<figureCitation box="[1204,1270,1924,1950]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1742,1766]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,273,1719]" captionTargetId="figure-64@4.[151,1435,273,1719]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–12. Hyperbius geniculatus (Signoret). 7. Dorsal View. 8. Head. Fig. 9. Metapleura. 10. Pendergrast’s Organ. 11. Female genitalia. Caudal view. 12. Male genitalia. Caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4692793" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4692793/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="671">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) with two longitudinal pale yellowish lines behind the ocelli and a rounded spot between them of the same color, all them well marked. Dorsally with thick, well-defined punctures. Mandibular plates just surpassing the apex of the anteclypeus. Antennae with the segment I exceeding the apex of the head. Female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1075,1159,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1742,1766]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,273,1719]" captionTargetId="figure-64@4.[151,1435,273,1719]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–12. Hyperbius geniculatus (Signoret). 7. Dorsal View. 8. Head. Fig. 9. Metapleura. 10. Pendergrast’s Organ. 11. Female genitalia. Caudal view. 12. Male genitalia. Caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4692793" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4692793/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="672">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
). First gonocoxae wide, black, markedly rough longitudinally; second gonocoxae semicircular, dark brown, with transverse roughness; paratergite 9 subtriangular, apically acute, black and rough, with outer margin clear and smooth.
</paragraph>
